---
import FeatureCard from './FeatureCard.astro';
---

<section class="py-20 sm:py-28 bg-white dark:bg-gray-950">
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-7xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
    <div class="text-center mb-16">
      <h2 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-extrabold text-gray-900 dark:text-white tracking-tight">
        Why isHistory?
      </h2>
      <p class="mt-4 text-lg text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 max-w-3xl mx-auto">
        Technology is built by humans — messy, brilliant, contradictory humans who argue, fail, change their minds, and occasionally stumble into breakthroughs. But most tech history forgets that. It gives you dates, specs, product launches, and code repositories. It tells you <em class="text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200">what</em> happened, but never <em class="text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200">how</em> — or <em class="text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200">why</em>.
      </p>
      <p class="mt-4 text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white max-w-3xl mx-auto">
        isHistory is different. We don't document code. We document the story behind the code.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="grid gap-8 sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3">
      <FeatureCard
        color="indigo"
        icon='<svg class="h-6 w-6" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M12 6.253v13m0-13C10.832 5.477 9.246 5 7.5 5S4.168 5.477 3 6.253v13C4.168 18.477 5.754 18 7.5 18s3.332.477 4.5 1.253m0-13C13.168 5.477 14.754 5 16.5 5c1.747 0 3.332.477 4.5 1.253v13C19.832 18.477 18.247 18 16.5 18c-1.746 0-3.332.477-4.5 1.253" /></svg>'
        title="Stories, Not Code"
        description="We don't archive repositories or commit logs. We document the human decisions, arguments, and accidents behind every breakthrough — from the first stored-program computer to the latest large language model."
      />
      <FeatureCard
        color="purple"
        icon='<svg class="h-6 w-6" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M9 20l-5.447-2.724A1 1 0 013 16.382V5.618a1 1 0 011.447-.894L9 7m0 13l6-3m-6 3V7m6 10l4.553 2.276A1 1 0 0021 18.382V7.618a1 1 0 00-.553-.894L15 4m0 13V4m0 0L9 7" /></svg>'
        title="Map the Digital Past"
        description="History isn't a list of inventions. It's a network of choices — wrong turns, brilliant failures, and forgotten pioneers. We map how we got here, so we don't repeat mistakes blindly."
      />
      <FeatureCard
        color="cyan"
        icon='<svg class="h-6 w-6" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M9.663 17h4.673M12 3v1m6.364 1.636l-.707.707M21 12h-1M4 12H3m3.343-5.657l-.707-.707m2.828 9.9a5 5 0 117.072 0l-.548.547A3.374 3.374 0 0014 18.469V19a2 2 0 11-4 0v-.531c0-.895-.356-1.754-.988-2.386l-.548-.547z" /></svg>'
        title="For the Curious, Not Just the Experts"
        description="No computer science degree required. Every series is written for a general audience: narrative first, jargon last. You'll understand the why without wrestling with code."
      />
      <FeatureCard
        color="emerald"
        icon='<svg class="h-6 w-6" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M19 20H5a2 2 0 01-2-2V6a2 2 0 012-2h10a2 2 0 012 2v1m2 13a2 2 0 01-2-2V7m2 13a2 2 0 002-2V9a2 2 0 00-2-2h-2m-4-3H9M7 16h6M7 8h6v4H7V8z" /></svg>'
        title="One Story at a Time"
        description="From deep dives like our 75-article Minds & Machines on AI to shorter origin tales, we publish weekly. Future series will cover the internet, personal computing, open source, and more."
      />
      <FeatureCard
        color="rose"
        icon='<svg class="h-6 w-6" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M4.318 6.318a4.5 4.5 0 000 6.364L12 20.364l7.682-7.682a4.5 4.5 0 00-6.364-6.364L12 7.636l-1.318-1.318a4.5 4.5 0 00-6.364 0z" /></svg>'
        title="Human Always"
        description="Behind every architecture, every algorithm, every crash is a person — brilliant, flawed, and often forgotten. We bring those lives back into the frame."
      />
      <FeatureCard
        color="amber"
        icon='<svg class="h-6 w-6" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M12 6.253v13m0-13C10.832 5.477 9.246 5 7.5 5S4.168 5.477 3 6.253v13C4.168 18.477 5.754 18 7.5 18s3.332.477 4.5 1.253m0-13C13.168 5.477 14.754 5 16.5 5c1.747 0 3.332.477 4.5 1.253v13C19.832 18.477 18.247 18 16.5 18c-1.746 0-3.332.477-4.5 1.253" /></svg>'
        title="No Code Required"
        description="This is not a developer's manual. It's a history book for the digital age — built for anyone who has ever wondered how did we actually get here?"
      />
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
